properties.dialogueText: "This time the Gateway Pistol won't help you. Let's check how good you became."
"Marvellous! I think you're ready for your job!"
"I don't hate you. But now you can leave. See you, Dry."
"Hey! What are you doing there?"
"Dry. Please. Come back here. There is a little misunderstanding between us."
"I had to test you. To get you ready for your work!"
"I see that you're good with the Gateway Pistol but... that's not the point!"
"You had to... live an experience. Solve problems. Risk something... well..."
"...probably your life is quite too much but... Hey! Listen..."
"Life and job happens every day, at the same time. Well... probably losing your job is not like losing your life. We've to improve that part of the training program... Details! But..."
"You've decided to leave the Gateway S.R.L. Good. I won't try to stop you again. But remember what you've truly learned from all this. Bye, Dry. See you around, one day."

"Welcome to Life Corp.! The best company EVER! Your curriculum mentions only one skill - you don't have motion sickness! Your previous experience with the Gateway Pistol is quite forgettable - competitors are so weak nowadays. In your stage you'll learn how to use the Life Thrower. Believe me... You'll have great fun!"
"I'll eat this delicious chocolate cake while watching you jumping around."
"...this cherry on the top is funny."
"...and there are a lot of layers! Yum!"
"... Okay. I was lying. I'm not eating any cake. Probably I don't have any mouth. Anyway... It's the time."
"No hints this time."
"Figure it out by yourself."
"Will you get out of this room?"
"Okay. I'll help you. You've to keep the buttons pressed. See. It's easy."
"You followed my tips and won. You've to be proud of yourself! Well done!"
"You have arrived to the ninth room! This one is... Aw. Easy. An easy one. For relaxing. Good job."
"Aw! The eight room! This is an hard one! Stay there, I'm coming to help you."
"I'm coooming..."
"Okay. I'm here.. Aw. You already reached at the exit by yourself... Okay. I'm not offended. Go on."
"Aw! Your fellow trainer! You'd be lost without him! Here it comes for helping you!"
"See? Now try to do it by yourself."
"Learning is fun! Isn't it?"
"I can't find it on your curriculum anyway. Do you have motion sickness?"
"Aw, sorry. You don't have any curriculum."
"Very well! Your first curriculum entry! No motion sickness! We're progressing well!"
"Mistakes are like... lasers. Yeah. They can melt you. For real."
"I'm kidding. Errors aren't like lasers. They are important for learning. If you're not doing it wrong, you're not a good learner. Next time, jump on lasers."
"Have I mentioned that work can kill you?"
"A little advice by someone older than you. Momentum is transfered while crossing gateways. Just that."
"Very well. My advices are cool, isn't it? You're learning fast!"
"Oh, you failed. But don't worry. Failing is important for learning. Now, try again!"
"Woops. Are you ok? Looks like we are missing an elevator here. Anyway..."
"Use the stairs to reach the next test."
"Woops. Stairs are broken. Please, wait your trainer here."
"Very well! You're already here! I can let the trainer go for its coffee, then."
"Good! Good."
"Ok. This is your first test. For you, no hints. Reach the door!"
"Well done. Well done..."
"You obviously need to find a button to shut down this wall."
"Time to learn how to use your Gateway Pistol! Just go on that platform! Don't be shy!"
"Now you're the king! Use direction buttons and A or B for shooting colorful bullets! Pew pew! Shoot at the cameras!"
"Bored already? You're so resourceful! Hit that button and go ahead!"
"Woops! That button isn't working well. Just stay there. Your trainer will come shortly."
"Please! Stay still! Watch out for the lasers!"
"It's coming! It's coming! You're so hyperactive! I like you!"
"I like your way of thinking! You need better challenges. Well... I'll give you what you need to become a real professional!"
"Welcome to Gateways S.R.L., fellow intern!"
"Your name is Dry, right? Hello Dry! Get ready to join the wonderful world of having a job! I've to check few things before we get started! Please, come in!"
"Very well, Dry! You already have our Gateway Pistol! Not bad! Not bad! Please, proceed!"
"Are we ready? Yes, we are! Now wait here. Your personal and professional trainer will open the door for you! Aren't you excited?"
